Obstacle Avoiding Robot:-
This is a robot car made using Arduino Uno (or similar Arduino boards). The robot can move on its own and avoid obstacles using an ultrasonic sensor and a servo motor that scans the surroundings.

Features:-

1)Autonomous Navigation
The robot moves forward by itself and detects obstacles in front of it.

2)Smart Scanning
The ultrasonic sensor is attached to a SG90 Servo Motor, which turns left and right to check for obstacles and find a clear path.

3)Obstacle Avoidance
If the robot detects something in front of it, it decides whether to turn left, right, or move backward.

4)Audio Feedback
An Active Buzzer makes a sound when the robot detects an obstacle.

5)Sensor Validation
The robot checks the sensor reading multiple times to make sure the obstacle detection is correct.


Components Needed:-

1. Arduino board (such as Arduino Uno or Arduino Nano)

2. L298N Motor Driver Module

3.  DC motors with wheels(total 4)

4. HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor

5. SG90 Servo Motor

6. Active buzzer

7. Robot chassis with wheels

8. Battery pack (7–12V recommended)

9. Jumper wires



